verbs.description: exect (third-person singular simple present exects, present participle execting, simple past and past participle exected)

entries.meaning: (transitive, obsolete) To cut off or out.
examples: the Office of the Spleen is of great importance, though it may be ſupplyed by other parts, in caſe it be diſeaſed, obſtructed, or exected
